data.description: Desirable Legend Oaks Planation in award winning DDII schools! Arguably, this is the best street in Legend Oaks! Quality built John Wieland homes on larger lots, on the golf course and long cul de sac. This home offers southern charm with brick front, welcoming front porch, live oak and magnolia trees. Rest of the home is sided with durable cement plank. Enter this executive home to the 2 story foyer. Hardwood flooring flows throughout the living areas. On the left find the office with vaulted ceiling and doors for privacy. To the right is the formal dining room, which also has access to the kitchen, making entertaining for large groups a breeze. Conitnue into the 2 story Great room with fireplace and built-ins and open to the kitchen. No space is wasted in this home. Kitchen offersample counter and cabinet space.  Maple cabinets. Granite counters. Tile floors, backsplash and wall on the bar. This is the ideal home for entertaining! Small gatherings can enjoy the eat-in kitchen and bar area while conversing with the cook. Continue the fun to the screened porch with vaulted ceiling with fan, or onto the stone patio with built in firepit and sitting walls. You will love the privacy, with wooded area between backyard, golf course and pond. Lot is a spacious .35 acres! Back inside find owners suite off family room, away from all other bedrooms. Owners bath is large with soaking garden tub, separate shower, linen closet, dual vanities, water closet and walk-in closet with custom shelving. Upstairs find 3 spacious bedrooms. The full bath connects the 2 front bedrooms with hall access for the 3rd bedroom. Front bedroom has custom built-in closet. Bedroom over the garage has 2 attic access doors for storage. Walk-in-storage is a rare find! The 3rd bedroom has hardwood flooring. This home has many great features, too numerous to mention, but provided upon request.  The paid off Solar panels is one of the features that will save you money! Garage has built-in shelving, great for storage. Plantation shutters, crown molding, the extra cabinets and racks in the bedrooms and laundry, tankless water heater, hardwood on stairs and landing. The only carpet is in owners closet and 2 upstairs bedrooms. Call for more details and to schedule your showing.  Pool and golf are not included in the HOA fee, but can be purchased separately. There are 2 pools available in Legend Oaks, both privately owned and not connected. You can choose to join a pool, tennis or golf, or not join any.
